# Ralph Runbook ŌĆö How to Intervene

Generated by the meta-ralph SKILL. Lives at `.ralph/RUNBOOK.md`. Edit freely; it's a guide, not a contract.

The contract is in `.ralph/prompt.md` (agent obligations) and the driver script's invariant checks (driver obligations). This file tells **you** (the human supervising the loop) what to do when something needs your attention.

---

## TL;DR

| I want to... | Do this |
|---|---|
| Start the loop | `{{RUN_COMMAND}}` (default: 10 iterations, agent's default model) |
| Run for N iterations | `{{RUN_COMMAND}} N` |
| Pin a specific model | `{{RUN_COMMAND}} --model claude-opus-4-7` (or whatever your agent CLI accepts) ŌĆö overrides any `--model` already in `prd.json.runner.args` (strip-then-append) |
| Both | `{{RUN_COMMAND}} 20 --model gpt-5.4` (any order; `--model=X` form also works) |
| Change CLI / default model / baseline flags | Edit `prd.json.runner` ŌĆö `command` is the binary to spawn, `args` is the argument list with `"{PROMPT}"` as the prompt placeholder. Required. Driver re-validates every iteration. |
| See current state | `cat prd.json` (or pipe through `jq`) |
| See what last iteration did | `tail -50 .ralph/progress.txt` |
| Stop gracefully (recommended) | `touch .ralph/.stop` from another terminal ŌĆö driver finishes current iter, exits 0 cleanly |
| Stop now (force) | `Ctrl+C` ŌĆö aborts mid-iteration, check `git status` after |
| Resume after stop | Re-run `{{RUN_COMMAND}} N` ŌĆö already-passed stories are skipped |
| Skip a stuck story | Edit `prd.json`: set its `status` to `blocked`, fill `notes` with the reason |
| Retry a blocked story | Edit `prd.json`: set its `status` back to `todo` |
| Drop a story permanently | Remove its entry from `prd.json.userStories[]` |
| Rewrite a story's scope | Edit its `description` / `acceptanceCriteria` in `prd.json`; set `status: todo` |

