## 1. Status Inspection

### `prd.json` ŌĆö source of truth

Each `userStories[i].status` is one of:

- **`todo`** ŌĆö agent will pick on next iteration (lowest `priority` first)
- **`in_progress`** ŌĆö agent claimed this; should transition before iteration ends
- **`passed`** ŌĆö done. Driver enforces this matches a real new commit (commit-verify invariant)
- **`blocked`** ŌĆö agent gave up; `notes` field has the reason. Your call to investigate

Quick counts:

```bash
# How many of each status?
jq '[.userStories[].status] | group_by(.) | map({status: .[0], count: length})' prd.json

# Which stories are blocked?
jq '.userStories[] | select(.status == "blocked") | {id, title, notes}' prd.json
```

### `.ralph/progress.txt`

Two parts:

1. **`## Codebase Patterns`** at the top ŌĆö consolidated learnings the agent has accumulated (library version pins, env quirks, refactoring tips, "do this / don't do that"). Read this before manually editing code so you stay consistent with what previous iterations established.
2. **Per-iteration blocks** ŌĆö what was implemented for each story, files changed, gotchas hit. Read these to understand why a story is stuck or what an earlier iteration discovered.

### `git log`

Each `passed` story corresponds to exactly one commit, message format `feat: US-NNN - <title>`. Quick audit:

```bash
git log --oneline feature-branch-name        # all commits since branch start
git log --grep "US-005"                       # find the commit for a specific story
git show <sha>                                # what that iteration actually changed
```

