## 5. OS Sleep / Hibernate During Long Runs

The driver is a synchronous `spawnSync` over the agent CLI. System suspend (laptop close, idle timeout, hibernate) freezes the entire driver + agent process. On wake, the agent CLI may have hit timeout, lost API session, or had network interrupted. Result: iteration may corrupt or simply fail.

**Suppress sleep before launching long runs:**

- **Windows:**

  ```powershell
  powercfg /change standby-timeout-ac 0
  powercfg /change standby-timeout-dc 0
  {{RUN_COMMAND}} N
  # restore afterwards (default standby is 30 min on AC):
  powercfg /change standby-timeout-ac 30
  powercfg /change standby-timeout-dc 30
  ```

  Or, if you have **PowerToys** installed, use the **Awake** module: tray icon ŌåÆ "Keep awake indefinitely" ŌåÆ run the loop ŌåÆ switch off when done.

- **macOS:**

  ```bash
  caffeinate -dimsu {{RUN_COMMAND}} N
  ```

- **Linux (systemd):**

  ```bash
  systemd-inhibit --what=sleep --why="ralph loop running" {{RUN_COMMAND}} N
  ```

If the loop *was* suspended mid-iteration: kill the driver (`Ctrl+C`), inspect `git status`, decide whether to keep partial work, then re-run.

> v2 plan: driver auto-detects OS and suppresses sleep itself for the duration of the run. See spec ┬¦7.3 (OS suspend row).

